<TITLE> Education policy sent for PM's vetting </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 12 (bdnew24.com)  The proposed education policy was sent to the prime minister on Thursday, officials said. "The draft policy has been sent to the prime minister at noon for approval," Subodh Chandra Dhali, public relations officer of the ministry, told bdnews24.com. He said the policy will be tabled at the cabinet after her approval. The policy was supposed to be tabled in the cabinet in December, but was deferred due to protests from different quarters including the religion-based groups. The government in April last year formed the policy formulation committee, led by Professor Kabir Chowdhury, which in September last year submitted the draft. bd
